# UCP Skill Taxonomy

When selecting skills, follow this hierarchy. Always read parent before child.

## Layer: transport
- unreal-client-protocol — UCP TCP/JSON communication layer, prerequisite for all others

## Layer: foundation
- unreal-object-operation — UObject property read/write, metadata, undo/redo
- unreal-asset-operation — Asset search, dependencies, CRUD, editor operations
- unreal-actor-editing — Actor spawn/delete/duplicate/move/select

## Layer: convention
- unreal-nodecode-common — Shared NodeCode graph-editing rules (read before any graph-editing skill)

## Layer: domain

### Graph Editing (parent: unreal-nodecode-common)
- unreal-material-editing — Material expression node graphs
- unreal-blueprint-editing — Blueprint node graphs, functions, events
- unreal-niagara-editing — Niagara VFX systems, emitters, modules
- unreal-widget-editing — UMG Widget Blueprint UI layouts

### Modeling (parent: unreal-modeling)
- unreal-modeling — GeometryScript entry point (read first, then sub-skills as needed)
  - unreal-modeling-primitives — Box, Sphere, Cylinder, sweep, revolve
  - unreal-modeling-meshops — Boolean, simplify, remesh, repair, subdivide
  - unreal-modeling-uv — UV projection, layout, transform
  - unreal-modeling-normals — Normals, tangents, flip, split
  - unreal-modeling-deform — Bend, twist, smooth, displace, transform
  - unreal-modeling-query — Bounding box, raycast, containment, sampling
  - unreal-modeling-selection — Select by sphere/box/plane/normal/material
  - unreal-modeling-attributes — Vertex color, polygroup, material ID
  - unreal-modeling-asset — Asset load/save, collision generation
  - unreal-modeling-create — Mesh generation and creation

## Layer: composite
- unreal-large-blueprint-analysis — Systematic large Blueprint analysis and C++ translation
- unreal-live-coding — Live Coding runtime C++ recompilation
- unreal-pie-control — Play In Editor / Simulate In Editor control

## Layer: workflow
- unreal-plugin-localization — Plugin UI text translation workflow

## Selection Rules
1. Determine the LAYER needed from user intent
2. Within domain, determine SUB-DOMAIN (graph-editing vs modeling)
3. Always load transport skill knowledge first if unsure about UCP calling convention
4. For graph editing: load convention skill (unreal-nodecode-common) before domain skill
5. For modeling: load unreal-modeling before any modeling sub-skill
